A woman in her 70s needed medical treatment after a dog bit her hand as she walked with a friend in a Derbyshire village.Police said the attack happened in Station Road, Draycott, at about 11:40 BST on 5 September.The pair had passed a man with a dog, believed to be a Rottweiler, when it attacked her.The injury is not thought to be serious but Derbyshire Police have appealed for witnesses.Follow BBC East Midlands on Facebook, on Twitter, or on Instagram. Send your story ideas to eastmidsnews@bbc.co.uk
